.TH CHECK_QIFTOP 1 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.4" "Monitoring Plugins"
.SH NAME
check_qiftop \- Nagios/Icinga/Zabbix monitoring plugin for qiftop network rates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B check_qiftop
.B \-\-warning
.I rate
.B \-\-critical
.I rate
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B check_qiftop
is a one\-shot monitoring plugin that queries the
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
over D\-Bus, samples a throughput metric, compares it with
.B \-\-warning
and
.B \-\-critical
thresholds, and prints Nagios plugin output (status plus performance data
after a
.RB \(lq | \(rq
separator).
.PP
It has no GUI dependency and runs as an unprivileged D\-Bus client. The
calling user must be able to access the
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)
system service, usually by being in the
.B netdev
group (see
.BR qiftop\-agent (8)).
.PP
The check waits for one or two poll samples so the rate is meaningful, then
exits. If no data arrives within
.B \-\-timeout
seconds it exits
.B UNKNOWN
rather than blocking the scheduler.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-warning " rate"
Warning threshold (required). Accepts bytes per second with an optional IEC
suffix:
.BR K / Ki ", " M / Mi ", " G / Gi
(e.g.
.BR 50Mi ).
.TP
.BI \-\-critical " rate"
Critical threshold (required). Must be \(>=
.BR \-\-warning .
.TP
.BI \-\-metric " name"
Metric to check:
.BR rate_in " (alias " rx_rate "), " rate_out " (alias " tx_rate "), or "
.BR rate_total " (alias " total_rate ", the default)."
.TP
.BI \-\-iface " name"
Restrict the check to a single network interface (e.g.
.BR eth0 ).
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-filter .
.TP
.BI \-\-filter " expr"
Restrict the check to flows matching a qiftop filter expression, aggregating
their rate. For a per\-interface flow check use
.BR "\-\-filter iface=<name>" .
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-iface .
.TP
.B \-\-session
Talk to the agent on the D\-Bus
.I session
bus instead of the system bus (development/testing).
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " seconds"
Maximum time to wait for live data before returning
.B UNKNOWN
(default 10).
.TP
.BI \-\-interval\-ms " ms"
Agent poll cadence to request while sampling (default 1000).
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
Standard Nagios plugin codes:
.TP
.B 0
OK \(em metric below the warning threshold.
.TP
.B 1
WARNING \(em metric at/above warning but below critical.
.TP
.B 2
CRITICAL \(em metric at/above the critical threshold.
.TP
.B 3
UNKNOWN \(em bad arguments, the agent was unreachable, or no data within the timeout.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Warn at 50\ MiB/s, crit at 100\ MiB/s on the total rate of
.BR eth0 :
.PP
.RS
.EX
check_qiftop \-\-iface eth0 \-\-metric rate_total \-\-warning 50Mi \-\-critical 100Mi
.EE
.RE
.PP
Alert on a container's outbound rate (flows scoped with the filter language):
.PP
.RS
.EX
check_qiftop \-\-filter 'runtime=docker' \-\-metric rate_out \-\-warning 20Mi \-\-critical 80Mi
.EE
.RE
.PP
Typical Nagios output line:
.PP
.RS
.EX
QIFTOP WARNING \- eth0 total 95.4 MiB/s | total_rate=100063026B/s;52428800;104857600;0
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR qiftop (1),
.BR nqiftop (1),
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5)
.SH AUTHOR
The qiftop project \(em <https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop>.
